Issues.Body:
Environment

  - Tailwind CSS Version: v4.1.18
  - Plugin: @tailwindcss/vite v4.1.18
  - Browser: Chrome 131 (latest), Firefox 133
  - Build Tool: Vite 6.0

#  Description

  Tailwind v4.1.18 generates invalid color-mix() syntax when compiling utility classes with opacity modifiers (e.g., bg-white/70, bg-gray-800/80). The percentage values are missing the % symbol, causing browsers to ignore the rules entirely.

  **Expected Behavior**

  When using opacity modifiers like bg-white/70, Tailwind should generate:
```css
  .bg-white\/70 {
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, #fff 70%, transparent);
  }
```

  **Actual Behavior**

  Tailwind generates invalid syntax:
```css
  .bg-white\/70 {
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, #fff .7, transparent);
  }
```
  Note: .7 instead of 70% - this is invalid and browsers ignore it.

# Reproduction

  **Step 1: Install Tailwind v4.1.18**
  > npm install tailwindcss@4.1.18 @tailwindcss/vite@4.1.18

  **Step 2: Configure vite.config.js**
```js
  import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
  import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';

  export default defineConfig({
    plugins: [tailwindcss()],
  });
```

  **Step 3: Use opacity utilities in HTML**
```html
  <div class="bg-white/70 text-gray-900/80 border-blue-500/50">
    Opacity not working
  </div>
```

  **Step 4: Check compiled CSS**
```css
  /* Generated (INVALID) */
  .bg-white\/70 {
    background-color: color-mix(in srgb, #fff .7, transparent);
  }

  .text-gray-900\/80 {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, oklch(21% .034 264.665) .8, transparent);
  }

  .border-blue-500\/50 {
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, oklch(62.3% .214 259.815) .5, transparent);
  }
```

  **Impact**

  - All opacity modifiers (/10, /20, /50, /80, etc.) fail silently in browsers
  - Chrome DevTools shows rules as crossed out (invalid)
  - Affects background colors, text colors, borders, shadows, and any property using opacity

  **Affected Utilities**

  - `bg-{color}/{opacity}` - e.g., `bg-red-500/50`
  - `text-{color}/{opacity}` - e.g., `text-blue-600/70`
  - `border-{color}/{opacity}` - e.g., `border-gray-300/30`
  - Custom classes using @apply with opacity utilities

  Workaround

  Manually override with valid syntax:

```css
  .bg-white\/70 {
    background-color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.7) !important;
  }
```

  Or use the modern RGB syntax directly:
```css
  .custom-class {
    background-color: rgb(255 255 255 / 0.7);
  }
```


  This appears to be a regression from v3.x, where opacity modifiers worked correctly.


  The color-mix() generator should output:
  - 70% instead of .7
  - 80% instead of .8
  - 50% instead of .5

**What version of Tailwind CSS are you using?**

v4.1.18

**What build tool (or framework if it abstracts the build tool) are you using?**

Astro 5.16.6 (uses Vite internally)

**What version of Node.js are you using?**

v24.12.0

**What browser are you using?**

N/A (build-time issue)

**What operating system are you using?**

macOS

